New York City has begun a new attempt of sifting through debris of the World Trade Center to find human remains from the 9/11 attacks after outcry from victims' families who still have nothing to bury.

The work began Monday. It's expected to continue for about 10 weeks at the Fresh Kills landfill in Staten Island.

Deputy Mayor Cas Holloway said in a memo on Friday that DNA testing will continue until every possible victim identification can be made.

