City officials say about 60 truckloads of construction debris have been collected around the site over the past two and a half years.

Some 2,750 people died at the World Trade Center in the 2001 attacks carried out by al Qaeda terrorists who crashed hijacked airliners into the buildings.

So far, 1,634 people have been positively identified.

